EU Legislators Likely to Back Single Patent Regime, FT Reports

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-02-15T07:51:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/eu-legislators-likely-to-back-single-patent-regime-ft-reports.html
European legislators are likely to
vote for a single European patent regime today, even if not all
of the European Union’s 27 member-countries support it, the
Financial Times reported.  Spain and  Italy  aren’t in agreement with the proposed
translation regime, which would focus on French, German and
English, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in  London  on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story
Colin Keatinge in London at   ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 